A MAN has been arrested after a child was abducted.
The 39-year-old man is expected to appear in court tomorrow after the child was approached and abducted for a short time in Bonnybridge, near Falkirk, yesterday evening.
Police Scotland is appealing for information from anyone who noticed anything suspicious in the area of Woodburn Crescent, Bonnybridge.
DI Hugh Louden said: &quot;I would like to reassure the community that we have a man in custody and there is no danger to members of the public. Anyone who does have concerns or would like to report any suspicious activity, should contact Police Scotland on 101 or Crimestoppers on 0800 555 111.&quot;
